[I] Raid Configuration Tool

[T] mdadm is a tool for creating, managing and monitoring
[T] device arrays using the "md" driver in Linux, also
[T] known as Software RAID arrays

[A] Neil Brown
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

[C] extra/filesystem
[F] CROSS DIETLIBC

[L] GPL
[V] 4.6

